-- Run this in Supabase SQL Editor to update T&C and House Rules to warehouse/storage versions

UPDATE templates
SET data = data || jsonb_build_object(
  'name', 'Terms and Conditions',
  'version', 'v2.0',
  'updatedAt', '2026-05-15',
  'content', '<h2>Warehouse &amp; Storage Licence Agreement — Terms &amp; Conditions</h2><h3>1. Definitions</h3><p>In this Agreement: <strong>"Agreement"</strong> means this Warehouse &amp; Storage Licence Agreement; <strong>"Commencement Date"</strong> means the start date in the Key Details; <strong>"End Date"</strong> means the end date in the Key Details; <strong>"HexaHub"</strong> means HexaHub Pty Ltd; <strong>"House Rules"</strong> means the Found Huntingdale House Rules as amended from time to time; <strong>"Interest Rate"</strong> means 2% per month or the maximum rate permitted by law; <strong>"Licence Fee"</strong> means the monthly fee in the Key Details; <strong>"Licensee"</strong> means the party identified on page 1; <strong>"Premises"</strong> means the warehouse or storage unit at Found Huntingdale, 17–31 Franklyn Street, Huntingdale VIC 3166; <strong>"Security Deposit"</strong> means the deposit amount in the Key Details.</p><h3>2. Term</h3><p>(a) This Agreement commences on the Commencement Date and continues until the End Date, unless terminated earlier. (b) Unless either party provides written notice of non-renewal no later than the Minimum Notice Period prior to the End Date, this Agreement will automatically renew for a further term equal to the original Service Term, subject to any Licence Fee adjustment.</p><h3>3. Permitted Use</h3><p>(a) The Licensee is granted a licence to occupy and use the Premises solely for lawful warehousing, storage, fulfilment, and light industrial operations directly related to the Licensee''s business. The Premises must not be used for retail, residential, or any purpose not approved in writing by HexaHub. (b) This Agreement is a licence only and does not create a tenancy, lease, or any right of exclusive possession at law.</p><h3>4. HexaHub Obligations</h3><p>HexaHub agrees to provide access to the Premises and to maintain the structural integrity of the building, common driveways, and shared services in good repair throughout the Service Term. HexaHub may relocate the Licensee to a comparable unit on 30 days'' written notice where reasonably required.</p><h3>5. Licensee Obligations</h3><p>(a) The Licensee agrees to: (i) comply with this Agreement and the House Rules; (ii) use the Premises only for the Permitted Use; (iii) keep the Premises clean, safe, and in good condition; (iv) not carry out structural alterations without prior written consent; (v) ensure all employees, contractors, and visitors comply with this Agreement; (vi) maintain all required regulatory licences and permits; (vii) not sublet the Premises without prior written consent; and (viii) comply with the Occupational Health and Safety Act 2004 (Vic), Environmental Protection Act 2017 (Vic), and Dangerous Goods Act 1985 (Vic). (b) The Licensee must provide evidence of regulatory compliance upon HexaHub''s request.</p><h3>6. Security Deposit</h3><p>(a) The Licensee must pay the Security Deposit prior to the Commencement Date. HexaHub may apply the Deposit to any amounts owing. The Deposit cannot substitute for Licence Fee payments. (b) Subject to deductions, the Deposit will be refunded within 60 days of expiry or termination and fulfillment of all obligations.</p><h3>7. Fees, Payment &amp; Invoicing</h3><p>(a) <strong>Licence Fee:</strong> Payable monthly in advance on the first day of each month by direct bank transfer. (b) <strong>Late Payment:</strong> If unpaid for 5 business days after the due date, HexaHub may charge interest at the Interest Rate, a $80 late fee, suspend access, and/or terminate. (c) <strong>GST:</strong> All amounts are exclusive of GST. (d) <strong>Annual Adjustment:</strong> The Licence Fee is reviewed annually. HexaHub will provide 30 days'' notice. Increases are capped at 8%, with a minimum of 3% or CPI (whichever is greater). (e) <strong>Exit Fee:</strong> Payable upon expiry or termination within 7 days of invoice. (f) <strong>Direct Debit:</strong> If any invoice is unpaid for 14+ days, the Licensee irrevocably authorises HexaHub to debit nominated accounts with 2 business days'' notice.</p><h3>8. Access</h3><p>HexaHub may enter the Premises on reasonable written notice for inspections, maintenance, showing to prospective Licensees, or any other reasonable purpose.</p><h3>9. Alterations &amp; Fit-Out</h3><p>(a) No structural alterations may be made without prior written approval. All works must be by licensed contractors in compliance with the Building Act 1993 (Vic). (b) The Premises must be restored to original condition at the end of the Service Term at the Licensee''s cost.</p><h3>10. Insurance</h3><p>(a) The Licensee must maintain: (i) public liability insurance — minimum $20,000,000 per occurrence; (ii) workers'' compensation insurance as required by law; and (iii) goods and equipment insurance for full replacement value. Evidence must be provided to HexaHub upon request. (b) HexaHub''s insurance does not cover the Licensee''s property. HexaHub is not responsible for loss or damage to the Licensee''s goods.</p><h3>11. Termination</h3><p>HexaHub may terminate immediately if: (a) Licence Fees remain unpaid for 5 business days after notice; (b) the Licensee breaches this Agreement and fails to remedy within 14 days; (c) the Premises are used for an unlawful purpose; (d) insolvency proceedings are commenced; or (e) the Licensee causes material damage or poses a safety risk.</p><h3>12. Effect of Termination or Expiry</h3><p>(a) The Licensee must vacate, return credentials, remove all property, and restore the Premises within 5 business days. All amounts become immediately due. Property left after 5 business days is deemed abandoned. (b) If terminated due to the Licensee''s breach, the Licensee remains liable for Licence Fees for the balance of the Service Term.</p><h3>13. Liability &amp; Indemnity</h3><p>(a) To the extent permitted by law, HexaHub is not liable for loss of or damage to the Licensee''s goods, business interruption, indirect loss, or acts of third parties. (b) The Licensee indemnifies HexaHub from all claims arising from its use of the Premises, breach of this Agreement, injury or damage caused by its personnel, or environmental contamination.</p><h3>14. General</h3><p>(a) <strong>Governing Law:</strong> Victoria, Australia. (b) <strong>Entire Agreement:</strong> This Agreement and the House Rules are the entire agreement between the parties. (c) <strong>Severability:</strong> Invalid provisions are severed; the remainder continues. (d) <strong>Assignment:</strong> The Licensee must not assign without prior written consent. (e) <strong>Notices:</strong> In writing by email, effective on receipt.</p>'
),
updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'tmpl1';

UPDATE templates
SET data = data || jsonb_build_object(
  'name', 'House Rules',
  'version', 'v2.0',
  'updatedAt', '2026-05-15',
  'content', '<h2>Found Huntingdale — House Rules</h2><p>These House Rules govern the use of Found Huntingdale at 17–31 Franklyn Street, Huntingdale VIC 3166, operated by HexaHub Pty Ltd. They apply to all Licensees, employees, contractors, agents, and visitors. HexaHub may amend these Rules with reasonable notice.</p><h3>1. Access &amp; Security</h3><p>Access is available 24 hours a day, 7 days a week via electronic credentials. Credentials must not be shared, duplicated, or transferred to unauthorised persons. Loss or compromise of credentials must be reported to HexaHub in writing immediately. Replacement fees apply. All visitors must register at the access point. The Licensee is responsible for all visitors to their unit.</p><h3>2. Loading, Deliveries &amp; Vehicle Movements</h3><p>All loading and unloading must use designated loading docks and access points. Vehicles must not obstruct driveways, access roads, loading areas, fire lanes, or emergency exits at any time. Large vehicle movements (semi-trailers, B-doubles) must be pre-approved and coordinated with HexaHub to avoid peak access periods. Forklifts and pallet jacks are permitted within allocated units and designated loading areas only. All operators must hold current licences and certifications. HexaHub accepts no liability for deliveries made in common areas.</p><h3>3. Parking</h3><p>Allocated parking is for the Licensee''s personnel only. Vehicles must not be parked in fire lanes, loading zones, or in a manner obstructing access. Unauthorised vehicles may be towed without notice at the owner''s expense. Overnight vehicle storage and trailer storage require prior written approval and may incur additional charges.</p><h3>4. Prohibited Items &amp; Hazardous Materials</h3><p>The following are strictly prohibited without written authorisation from HexaHub:</p><ul><li>Flammable, explosive, or combustible materials beyond quantities permitted under the Dangerous Goods Act 1985 (Vic)</li><li>Toxic, corrosive, radioactive, or chemically reactive substances</li><li>Illegal goods, stolen property, or contraband</li><li>Firearms, weapons, or ammunition</li><li>Livestock or animals (except approved assistance animals)</li><li>Goods producing excessive odour, dust, or noise affecting other Licensees</li></ul><p>Licensees handling regulated dangerous goods must provide current compliance documentation upon request. Any chemical spill or environmental incident must be reported to HexaHub and relevant authorities immediately.</p><h3>5. Fire Safety &amp; Emergency Procedures</h3><p>Fire exits, extinguisher access points, sprinkler systems, and evacuation routes must remain unobstructed at all times. Storage within 600mm of any sprinkler head is prohibited. A clear evacuation path must be maintained within the unit. In an emergency, evacuate immediately, call 000, and notify HexaHub. Do not re-enter until cleared by emergency services. Hot works (welding, cutting, grinding) require a written permit from HexaHub at least 48 hours in advance. Fire safety equipment within the unit must be maintained by the Licensee.</p><h3>6. Structural Alterations &amp; Fit-Out</h3><p>No structural alterations, drilling, or modifications to walls, floors, ceilings, roller doors, or building services may be made without prior written consent. All approved works must be performed by licensed tradespeople in compliance with the Building Act 1993 (Vic) and applicable Australian Standards. The Licensee bears all costs including council approvals. The unit must be restored to original condition at the Licensee''s cost upon vacating.</p><h3>7. Waste Management &amp; Cleanliness</h3><p>All waste must be disposed of in designated areas and bins. Bulk waste and pallets must be broken down and placed in recycling areas. Waste must not be placed in driveways or car parks. Hazardous and chemical waste must be disposed of per Victorian regulations and must not enter general waste. Units must be kept clean and tidy. HexaHub may charge a cleaning fee for units left in an unsatisfactory condition.</p><h3>8. Noise &amp; Hours of Operation</h3><p>Noise-generating activities (heavy machinery, power tools, loading equipment) must occur between 7:00 AM and 9:00 PM Monday to Saturday. Activities outside these hours require prior written approval. Operations must not unreasonably interfere with other Licensees or neighbouring properties. The Licensee must comply with all EPA noise guidelines.</p><h3>9. Maintenance &amp; Reporting</h3><p>Any damage to the unit, building services, roller doors, or common areas must be reported to HexaHub in writing promptly. The Licensee maintains the interior of their unit in good condition. HexaHub maintains structural elements, common areas, and building services outside the unit boundary.</p><h3>10. Compliance with Laws</h3><p>Licensees must comply with all applicable laws including the Occupational Health and Safety Act 2004 (Vic), Environmental Protection Act 2017 (Vic), Dangerous Goods Act 1985 (Vic), Building Act 1993 (Vic), and Workplace Injury Rehabilitation and Compensation Act 2013 (Vic). The Premises must not be used for any unlawful purpose. HexaHub may immediately suspend or terminate access upon identification of a breach.</p>'
),
updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'tmpl2';
